'''Alexander Sdvizhkov''' is a [[Belarus]]ian journalist. He is the deputy chief editor for Zgoda, a weekly periodical.<ref name=Fox/>

Sdvizhkov was jailed for 3 years for printing cartoons of the Muslim prophet [[Muhammad]].<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Belarus_sentences_journalist_over_Mohammed_cartoons/articleshow/2712988.cms Belarus sentences journalist over Mohammed cartoons]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080123220528/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Belarus_sentences_journalist_over_Mohammed_cartoons/articleshow/2712988.cms |date=January 23, 2008 }}</ref> "We did the right thing by speaking out against Islamic hysteria," Sdvizhkov said.<ref name=Fox>{{Cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,185709,00.html |title=Belarus Paper Reprints Muhammad Cartoons  |access-date=2008-01-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5v9eeR73v?url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,185709,00.html |archive-date=2010-12-22 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> He is currently being held at the Belarusian Interior Ministry's transfer prison in [[Minsk]], with no means of communication and no date set to hear his appeal.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,331188,00.html |title=Freedom Remains Elusive for Journalist in Belarus Jailed for Printing Islamic Cartoons  |access-date=2008-02-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5v9egUSOS?url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,331188,00.html |archive-date=2010-12-22 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> The arrest is the first arrest in Europe since the [[Danish cartoons]] issue came up.

